10_wave_period


  1. Question

    A sinusoidal wave is graphed below.


    Estimate the period of the sinusoidal function graphed above.


    Solution

    Find the time difference between corresponding points in sequential repetitions.


    \[P~=~ (2.3)-(-4.1)\] \[P = 6.4\]

    This exact function could be plotted with the following algebraic definition: \[y(t) = 2 \sin\left(\frac{2\pi}{6.4}(t+2.5)\right)+(1.7)\]

    The amplitude is 2; the period is 6.4; the horizontal shift is left by 2.5; and the midline is \(y=1.7\).
